Introduction

WeNU is a South Korean boy group formed by Irion Entertainment. The group originally debuted as a five-member act on November 30, 2022, with the digital single "Haru Haru."
On June 14, 2023, Irion Entertainment announced that member Eden had officially left the group due to health concerns.

Three days later, on June 17, 2023, during a special post commemorating their 200th day since debut, WeNU revealed their official fandom name: WeGO.
